  "prompt": "Is a passport compulsory to travel on flights within India?",
  "response": "No, a passport is not compulsory for domestic flights within India. Indian citizens can travel on domestic flights using other valid photo identification documents. Acceptable ID proofs include:\n\n- Aadhar card\n- Voter ID card\n- PAN card\n- Driving license\n- Government-issued ID card (for government employees)\n- Bank passbook with photograph\n- School/college ID card (for students)\n\nAlways check with the airline for any specific ID requirements and ensure that the ID you present is valid and matches the name on your flight booking.",
